A road in West Sussex has now re-opened after it was closed on Friday morning due to a collision involving four cars. Fire crews, police and ambulance attended the scene on the B2139 in Houghton, near Arundel, according to West Sussex Fire and Rescue Service. Motorists were asked to avoid the area. Sussex Police said the people involved sustained minor injuries. 
